# Subtitle Player — Environment Example (optional fallback)

**Recommended:** configure Base URL, API Key, and model in the **⚙ Settings** panel (saved to the user data directory). No `.env` required.

Use `.env` only when you want shared defaults (development, team templates). Copy to project root or `%APPDATA%\SubtitlePlayer\.env` for the desktop app.

**Model in `.env` is optional** — you can set the translate model in ⚙ Settings instead. Built-in default applies if neither is set.

```ini
# ── DashScope (Alibaba Cloud Bailian) ───────────────────────────────────────
DASHSCOPE_OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://dashscope.aliyuncs.com/compatible-mode/v1
DASHSCOPE_API_KEY=sk-your-dashscope-key-here
# TRANSLATE_MODEL=qwen3.6-flash   # optional — configure model in ⚙ Settings

# ── Optional: dedicated translate vars (override DASHSCOPE_*) ───────────────
# TRANSLATE_BASE_URL=https://dashscope.aliyuncs.com/compatible-mode/v1
# TRANSLATE_API_KEY=sk-your-key-here
# TRANSLATE_MODEL=qwen3.6-flash   # optional

# ── Optional: generic OpenAI-compatible fallback ────────────────────────────
# BASE_URL=https://api.example.com/v1
# API_KEY=sk-your-key-here
# SUMMARY_MODEL / FAST_MODEL / MAIN_MODEL also optional model fallbacks
```

**Priority per field:** panel settings → `.env` → built-in defaults. Panel changes apply immediately without restart.
